title: Qayamat
subTitle: Two close friends turn enemies when one becomes a criminal and the other, an IPS officer. Wronged by his friend, the criminal swears to take revenge once he returns from prison.

title: Prem Tapasya
subTitle: Devi decides to marry a man named Mohan after she realises he is her one true love. However, her brother tries to stop their marriage when he finds troubling information on him.

title: Somnath Jyotirlinga
subTitle: A dramatised chronicle depicting the historical circumstances of the inception and evolution of Somnath Temple, one of the twelve jyotirlinga shrines of Lord Shiva.

title: Bhuvan Shome
subTitle: A lonely bureaucrat goes on holiday to a village in Gujarat where a young peasant woman helps him see beyond his job and develop a newfound empathy for people.

title: Chandan Ka Palna
subTitle: Ajit's perfect marriage to Shobha turns upside down after she starts behaving strangely with him and his mother, leading to a disturbed life.

title: Samadhi
subTitle: Lakhan Singh gives up his life of crime when he falls in love and marries Champa. However, things take a turn when she falls sick and he is forced to become a criminal again.

title: Mera Gaon Mera Desh
subTitle: When Ajit, a former prisoner, learns of Jabbar who is terrorising the people of his village, he decides to stand up against him. However, things take a turn when Jabbar abducts Ajit's lover.

title: Batwara
subTitle: Amidst the fall of princely states in post-independence India, the friendship between aristocrat Vikram and a peasant is tested. Vikram turns vengeful after his brother is killed in a peasant colony.

title: Razia Sultan
subTitle: Razia Sultan, the first female ruler of the Delhi Sultanate, lands in trouble and loses her kingdom when she falls in love with Jamal-ud-Din Yakut, an Abyssinian slave.

title: Dost
subTitle: Maanav befriends Gopichand, a reformed thief, and helps him secure a job to turn his life around. However, Maanav suddenly disappears and returns just in time to support Gopichand during a crisis.

subTitle: Vijay, who owns a furniture store, is in love with Varsha. However, Vijay's life takes a drastic turn when she decides to marry his friend Vikram, a rich man, who promises her a better life.

title: Narsingh Avatar
subTitle: Bringing the best in cinema.

subTitle: Charandas and Chameli develop feelings for each other. However, caste differences lead their families to oppose their budding relationship.

subTitle: Troubles arise for Surajmukhi after her husband, Sultan, is gunned down and she and her daughter get abducted by goons. She tries her best to get revenge and escape with her child.

title: Kundan
subTitle: Thakur Shamsher Singh, a wealthy criminal, tries to befriend a newly-appointed police officer in order to gain his favour, only to find out that the policeman is immune to his tactics.

subTitle: A young hooligan who looks exactly like a murdered prince is taken to the palace and made to impersonate him. Schemes, however, go sideways as the young man seems to have plans of his own.
